## Description
The**&nbsp;Batch HTTP ingress&nbsp;**resource&nbsp;allows to trigger the execution of a Batch workflow via API.

> Note

As for the On-Demand case, both native and retro-compatibility modes are supported for the Request.

The Response, on the other hand, is always empty (Status: 200 OK) and not an XML file as in the on-demand case.

> Important

The BOM is not currently supported for batch workflows, so it is not possible to use it in API calls.

For more information on API integration, see: [Web Services Exposed by Batch Workflows](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/Web+Services+Exposed+by+Batch+Workflows).

## Additional creation parameters
None.

## Resource editor
None.

## Deploy parameters
![](data:image/png;base64,)

Section

Field

Description

**Configuration**

**Tenant**

Select the&nbsp;**Tenant** on which you want to deploy the resource from the drop-down menu.

**Workflow**

**Resource**

Select the Batch Workflow resource that will be triggered when calling this endpoint.

> Important

If the selected workflow has not been deployed on the selected tenant, a warning message is displayed.

**Endpoint**

**Path**

Enter the final part of the URL path to call.

For example: "EndpointName"; the resulting URL will be: *http://qa-aws-frnk-1-doxee-int.cloud.doxee.com/api/v1/ingress/batch/****EndpointName***

**Keys**

*(optional)* Select the [Ingress Credentials](/doxee-platform/docs/ingress-credentials-resource-reference) resource(s) to use for API authentication, if required.

> Note

Up to 10 API keys can be used at the same time to avoid expiration issues.

**Parallel requests**

Select the maximum number of allowed requests per second. The available options are:

- 3

- 5&nbsp;*(default)*

- 10

- 15

- 40

- 50

> Important

If the selected rate limit doesn't include autoscaling, a warning message is displayed. In this case, it's necessary to adjust the capacity manually.

> Tip

Click **Publish **to publish the release on the tenant.

Click **Deploy** to publish and enable the release on the tenant.
